To create a JavaScript function that extracts a three character code using regex from a given filename, you can use the following code snippet:

```javascript
function extractThreeCharCode(filename) {
  // Define the regex pattern to match the three-character code
  const regex = /(\w{3})\.usfm$/;

  // Test the filename against the regex pattern
  const match = filename.match(regex);

  if (match && match[1]) {
    // If a match is found, return the three-character code
    return match[1];
  } else {
    // If no match is found, return null or an appropriate message
    console.log("Invalid filename format or no three-character code found.");
    return null;
  }
}

// Example usage:
const filename = "57-1Jn.usfm";
const result = extractThreeCharCode(filename);
console.log(result); // Output: 1Jn
```

This function uses a regular expression (regex) to match the three-character code followed by the ".usfm" extension in the filename. If a match is found, it returns the extracted code; otherwise, it logs an error message and returns `null`.
